<br>
Another thing that went right was our replacements.  We had a huge rash of cancels, some at the last minute, but were able to field 5 groups despite this.  The only crippling blow was the loss of both monk pullers.  Thanks go to Markk for steping in at the last minute and pulling for just over an hour.<br>
<br>
Congratz go out to Blodiron for winning the roll on the only drop of the evening.  He recieved boots off of the second kill of the night.<br>
<br>
Things I Learned:<br>
From a practical point of view this raid was a failure.  Sorry guys im not gonna sugar coat it.  All that effort and we get one drop. BAH!<br>
<br>
From a learning point of view this raid made significant headway.  <br>
<br>
I learned that you must be dubious or better faction to go here.  Camo and invis wont help this because many of the ToV mobs see invis.  7 pm cst at the wl zoneline&gt;<br>
<br>
Secondly we NEED a monk puller.  Despite Aabaral's valiant effort we did not get any mobs.  I wont comment beyond that statement.<br>
<br>
Thirdly almost everything that Wulfe said in the warm up confirmed the things that I found at Illia's Everquest Bestiary.<br>
He went beyond this with personal experience that enabled us to go as far as we did.<br>
<br>
Fourthly:  EVERYONE NEEDS TO LISTEN AND BE ON TIME.  There was some confusion before hand both in getting people there and then in buffing people up.  Next time we will not buff untill we are in HoT itself.  I will assign the raid channel for the gathering and then as people join their groups they will leave the raid channel and use the raid function.  This will help simplify communication a facilitate transportation.<br>
<br>
There will be additions to this list when i get home from work and i will try to  expand on what happened.  Hehe i didnt forget anyone yet i just dont have the time.<br>
<br>
VonAlbrecht Jaeger<br>
Guildleader Souls of Defiance <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bfederationofpovar.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilraafensalir>Kilraa Fensalir</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#70DB93>(2/28/03 11:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=114.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ToVHoT 27 feb</span><hr size=1> Thanks Von for leading this on a day that I could actually attend.  I greatly appreciate it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
