<br>
From a personal point of view I recognized how important the saves are now.  I have the SS bp now with some better saves and i purchased a pair of diamond rings which added to my saves.  This made a HUGE difference in the ammount of damage that I was taking.  I will be going into pop zones and looking for more/better resist gear. (where do all the bd drop Derko?  im calling another raid on that zone next! hehe)<br>
<br>
I agree also with the problem with the afk situation.  Guys I was there an HOUR AND A HALF before we went in and I had one afk and one log off/back on (sorry work paged and I have dial up).  If this was an 8 hour Fear raid I would understand more about afk's but it wasnt.  PLEASE get yourself set up before we zone in.  Dinner...pop...munchies...bathroom break...make out with the wife/husband/girl/boyfriend...feed the fish.... whatever please get it done before hand.<br>
<br>
As for the faction issue i agree with Raaddar.  SoD hosts a Kail faction night every wednesday so im going to throw the &quot;non kos&quot; deal in.  For the last couple weeks we have been able to get the bank but not had the forces to take an arena slot.  There are lots of named giants pulled  at the bank that deliver bigger faction hits.  Fildaar didnt go up to dubious or better with just one raid so you will need to attend several to get to this level or hit a nice 4 hour arena raid.  I got to ally in just over a week of hunting in Kael that included one nice stint in the arena (courtesy of MoS who raided there and allowed me to join them).<br>
<br>
One thing I would like to recognize is Wulfe's actions.  If you didnt know dragging bodies in HoT makes you DEAD.  The dragons take this action as a personal affront and will not hesitate to show their displeasure in a very physical way.  Wulfe did this not once but TWICE to get people to where Kilraa could rez them.  Between that and the guidance that he provided myself and the raid in general I am pleased to award him The Order of Defiant Souls.  This is the highest award that Souls of Defiance can bestow and Wulfe's actions during this raid are a credit to himself, his guild and the Federation.<br>
<br>
And while im on the matter of superb jobs done:  every healer in attendance is to be commended.  Up untill the wipe out i believe that we only had one death.  For HoT this is a very good record.  Every Evacker is also to be commended.  On an accidental aggro getting even half of the raid out was excellent work.  <br>
<br>
With that said guys I will let the matter rest.  I am sure that there are things that I have forgotten and I am just as confident that I will be reminded.  I will schedual another raid for this zone with better results from the things that I have learned from this one.<br>
